This method deserializes the specified Json into an object of the specified type. This method is useful if the specified object is a generic type. For non-generic objects, use parseObject(String, Class, Feature[]) instead. If you have the Json in a InputStream instead of a String, use parseObject(InputStream, Type, Feature[]) instead. 形参: json – the string from which the object is to be deserialized type – The specific genericized type of src.
